== Subphylum Trilobita

-   Extinct for 200 million years; flourished in Cambrian and Ordovician.
-   **Body Shape**: Trilobed (two longitudinal grooves).
-   **Tagmata**: Cephalon (head), Trunk, Pygidium.
-   **Appendages**: Biramous on each segment except the last.

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-19-4").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-19-4").caption
)

== Subphylum Chelicerata

-   **Tagmata**: Two; *Cephalothorax* (prosoma) and *Abdomen* (opisthosoma).
-   **Appendages**: Six pairs on cephalothorax.
    -   1 pair of **chelicerae** (mouthparts).
    -   1 pair of **pedipalps**.
    -   4 pairs of **walking legs**.
-   **No antennae**.
-   Most suck liquid food from prey.

