=== Class Pycnogonida (Sea Spiders)

-   Small, thin bodies; usually 4 pairs of long walking legs (some have 5-6 pairs).
-   **Ovigers**: Subsidiary legs in males for carrying eggs.
-   **Proboscis**: Long, suctorial mouthpart.
-   Reduced abdomen.

