== Subphylum Myriapoda

-   "Many footed".
-   **Tagmata**: Head and Trunk.
-   **Appendages**: Paired appendages on most trunk segments; uniramous.
-   **Respiration**: Tracheae.
-   **Excretion**: Malpighian tubules.

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-19-21").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-19-21").caption
)

=== Class Chilopoda (Centipedes)

-   Flattened bodies.
-   **Segments**: Each bears **one pair** of legs (except first and last two).
-   **Venom claws**: Modified appendages of first body segment (maxillipeds).
-   Carnivorous, active predators.

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-19-22").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-19-22").caption
)

=== Class Diplopoda (Millipedes)

-   Cylindrical bodies.
-   **Segments**: Abdominal segments have **two pairs** of legs (diplosegments).
-   Herbivorous or scavengers.
-   Slow-moving; roll into coil; repugnatorial glands.

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-19-23").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-19-23").caption
)

=== Class Pauropoda

-   Minute, soft-bodied.
-   Branched antennae.
-   No true eyes.
-   12 trunk segments, usually 9 pairs of legs.

=== Class Symphyla

-   Small, centipede-like.
-   Live in humus/leaf mold.
-   Spinnerets on 13th segment (in some descriptions) or posterior.

